                <h1>Understanding the Use of Scrim Backgrounds in Visual Arts</h1>
                <p>Scrim background refers to a lightweight, often translucent fabric used in theater, photography, and film to create versatile visual effects. When lit from the front, it appears opaque, while backlighting reveals hidden images or scenes. This duality of scrim backgrounds enhances storytelling and adds depth to visual presentations.</p>
